 36 -def read(handle, debug=0): 

 37      """Parses a single KEGG Pathway from given file handle. 
 38   
 39      Returns a single Pathway object.  There should be one and only 
 40      one pathway in each file, but there may well be pathological 
 41      examples out there. 
 42      """ 
 43      iterator = parse(handle, debug) 
 44      try: 
 45          first = next(iterator) 
 46      except StopIteration: 
 47          first = None 
 48      if first is None: 
 49          raise ValueError("No pathways found in handle") 
 50      try: 
 51          second = next(iterator) 
 52      except StopIteration: 
 53          second = None 
 54      if second is not None: 
 55          raise ValueError("More than one pathway found in handle") 
 56      return first

 60      """Returns an iterator over Pathway elements. 
 61   
 62      Arguments:

 64      - debug - integer for amount of debug information to print 
 65   
 66      This is a generator for the return of multiple Pathway objects. 
 67      """ 
 68      # Check handle 
 69      if not hasattr(handle, 'read'): 
 70          if isinstance(handle, str): 
 71              handle = StringIO(handle) 
 72          else: 
 73              exc_txt = "An XML-containing handle or an XML string " +\ 
 74                  "must be provided" 
 75              raise Exception(exc_txt) 
 76      # Parse XML and return each Pathway 
 77      for event, elem in \ 
 78              ElementTree.iterparse(handle, events=('start', 'end')): 
 79          if event == "end" and elem.tag == "pathway": 
 80              yield KGMLParser(elem).parse() 
 81              elem.clear()

 97          def _parse_entry(element): 
 98              new_entry = Entry() 
 99              for k, v in element.attrib.items(): 
100                  new_entry.__setattr__(k, v) 
101              for subelement in element.getchildren(): 
102                  if subelement.tag == 'graphics':

104                  elif subelement.tag == 'component': 
105                      _parse_component(subelement, new_entry) 
106              self.pathway.add_entry(new_entry)

118              entry.add_component(new_component)

120          def _parse_reaction(element): 
121              new_reaction = Reaction() 
122              for k, v in element.attrib.items(): 
123                  new_reaction.__setattr__(k, v) 
124              for subelement in element.getchildren(): 
125                  if subelement.tag == 'substrate': 
126                      new_reaction.add_substrate(int(subelement.attrib['id'])) 
127                  elif subelement.tag == 'product': 
128                      new_reaction.add_product(int(subelement.attrib['id'])) 
129              self.pathway.add_reaction(new_reaction)

131          def _parse_relation(element): 
132              new_relation = Relation() 
133              new_relation.entry1 = int(element.attrib['entry1']) 
134              new_relation.entry2 = int(element.attrib['entry2']) 
135              new_relation.type = element.attrib['type'] 
136              for subtype in element.getchildren(): 
137                  name, value = subtype.attrib['name'], subtype.attrib['value'] 
138                  if name in ('compound', 'hidden compound'): 
139                      new_relation.subtypes.append((name, int(value))) 
140                  else: 
141                      new_relation.subtypes.append((name, value)) 
142              self.pathway.add_relation(new_relation)
